The paper deals with handwriting recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of attention-based models is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of LSTMs, which are a type of neural network commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses experiments on a database, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
